---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/docs.astro';
const rawBase = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = rawBase.endsWith('/') ? rawBase : rawBase + '/';
---
<DocsLayout title="Installation" current="Installation">

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Installation</h1>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Clawsewitz can be installed as a Claude Code plugin via a one-line installer or manually with git.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="one-line">One-line installer (recommended)</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">On macOS or Linux, open a terminal and run:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robertsinke/clawsewitz/main/scripts/install.sh | bash</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">The installer detects your OS, clones the plugin to <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">~/.claude/plugins/local/clawsewitz/</code>, registers the marketplace, and installs the plugin. It checks for <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">git</code>, <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">node</code> (≥20), and the <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">claude</code> CLI before proceeding.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="manual">Manual install</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If you prefer to install manually:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-2 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/robertsinke/clawsewitz \</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary pl-4">~/.claude/plugins/local/clawsewitz</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Then register and install the plugin:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">claude plugin marketplace add ~/.claude/plugins/local/clawsewitz</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">claude plugin install clawsewitz@clawsewitz-local</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="updating">Updating</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Re-run the installer or pull manually:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">cd ~/.claude/plugins/local/clawsewitz && git pull</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">claude plugin update clawsewitz@clawsewitz-local</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="uninstalling">Uninstalling</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Remove the plugin from Claude Code and delete the files:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto flex flex-col gap-1">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">claude plugin uninstall clawsewitz@clawsewitz-local</code>
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">rm -rf ~/.claude/plugins/local/clawsewitz</code>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="verify">Verifying the installation</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Confirm clawsewitz is installed and accessible:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">claude plugin list | grep clawsewitz</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You should see:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">clawsewitz@clawsewitz-local  Version: 0.4.0  Status: ✔ enabled</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary">If you see a version number, you are ready to go. See the <a href={`${base}docs/quickstart`} class="text-prussian underline underline-offset-2">Quick Start</a> guide to run your first engagement.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-3" id="skills-only">Skills-only bundle</h2>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If you only want the strategy skills and framework library without agents, workflows, or hooks:</p>
<div class="relative rounded-lg bg-prussian-tint px-5 py-4 mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
  <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-text-primary">curl -fsSL https://robertsinke.github.io/clawsewitz/install-skills | bash</code>
</div>
<p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">This installs only the <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">skills/</code> and <code class="font-mono text-[13px] bg-prussian-tint px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">references/</code> directories. No agents, no slash commands, no hooks. Use when you want the 70 frameworks and stage logic inside your own orchestration.</p>

</DocsLayout>
